# Prompt File Storage

All pre-defined prompts must be saved as `.toml` files in `config/prompts/`.

## Required format

Each prompt file must contain exactly three fields:

```toml
name = "Human-Readable Name"
description = "One-line description of what this prompt does"
system = """
Full system prompt text passed to the LLM.
"""
```

## Rules

- File must be named using kebab-case matching the prompt name (e.g. `email-reply.toml`)
- All three fields (`name`, `description`, `system`) are required
- `system` must use a triple-quoted multiline string (`"""..."""`)
- Never store prompt content inline in source code — always reference the `.toml` file
- New bundled prompts must also be listed in `specs/prompts.md` under the Bundled Prompts table
